rs in the air. Benjamin's heart raced—not with envy, but with the thrill of witnessing something rare: fashion as conjuring, the way it could call forth wonder from even the most skeptical among them. The fairylight seemed to respond to every stitch and shimmer, alive with the pulse of the crowd.\n\n(5)  \nWhen the final model bowed low before the critics, Benjamin caught a fleeting smile—a silent understanding that he"